headline: Assessing U.S. Bancorp (USB) Valuation After Its Recent Share Price Rebound
summary: U.S. Bancorp (USB) has been quietly grinding higher, with the stock up about 9% over the past month and roughly 4% in the past week, catching more investors’ attention. headline: How Investors Are Reacting To U.S. Bancorp (USB) Profit Surge And Growing Fee Income Base
summary: In the past quarter, U.S. Bancorp reported an 18% jump in Q3 2025 net income to US$1.89 billion, driven by strong fee income growth across capital markets and trust and investment management services. An additional signal of confidence came as Mackenzie Financial Corp increased its U.S. Bancorp holdings by 13.3% in the second quarter, highlighting growing institutional interest in the bank’s fee-rich, diversified business model.
